  "description": [
    "SENTINEL 2SSSS V A8 a a WUNIT MD Thursday September 5 1957 City Delays 350000 Water Plan I RockvillesMayor and Council postponed decisions on installa tions and replacement of water mains In the city after a public hearing Thursday at which citi zens argued that Assessments on water lines should be deferred until sewer services are available There should be no assess ment for water lines along the sides of lots already serviced by lines running along the front boundaries The 330000 cost of the 36 water projects included in the 1957SB capital program will be financed from the citys 26 mil lion bond issue and paid back by front foot assessments at the rate of 20 cents a foot for new lines and 10 and five cents a foot for replacement of twoinch and four inch lines by larger lines The projects when approved will complete the water system up to 95 percent in existing streets now without service and rehabili tate lines in older sections of town up to 92 percent The Mayor and Council will con sider amending the charter to al low deferrment of assessments requested by a citizens group led by C D Gull and"
